page.title: 13TOWNSEND FARMHOUSE
page.content: This is a protected building of historical interest.On the roof there are two chimneys,one modern the other 16/17 century.The roof is made from old thatch.Just below this,on the right, a new drainpipe has been fitted.On the left ,at the bottom of the thatch there are two windows,these are not modern.There is also one window to the right, these are second floor windows.On the first floor there are four windows_three to the left,one to the right.Below the thatch there is a porch.The porch roof is also thatched.The thatch looks newer than the main thatch.Looking directly at the porch you can see a black wooden door.There is a string on the door which you pull.It's the bell. Julian Jelfs,age:11.
